      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 7:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". According to the ideas of the ancient world, it was impossible for the Israelites to maintain any religious exclusiveness when they intermarried with the heathen nations (cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Jdg 2:1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " b–3); the connubium carried with it an alliance of religion and worship, as for instance in the case of Solomon, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Kings 11:1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
